### "No I/O in pipeline/" invariant evaluation — ENDORSED
Phase 1's "no I/O in pipeline/" invariant was over-stated for the pre-Phase-4.5 reality. The single_entry_pipeline.md decision places phase modules under tools/pipeline/, and phases legitimately do I/O. The relaxation is correct architectural correction, not erosion. No need to split into tools/phases/ or pipeline/pure/ — that would add ceremony without solving a current problem.

### No-behavior-change verification — PASSES
Compared the deleted planPhase, devPhase, qaPhase, invokeAgent, safeCall, refreshCompletionId, and resolveRunArg bodies in the diff against the new modules.

- runPlanPhase preserves existing-feature short-circuit, prompt construction, dry-run null result, provider/tier selection, planner invocation, stderr truncation, feature re-read, intent patch, and log messages.
- runDevelopPhase preserves packet scan, completion refresh, topo sort, dependency failure behavior, dry-run continue behavior, developer/reviewer/rework invocations, lifecycle calls, force-approve fallback, completion identity, and result arrays.
- runVerifyPhase preserves QA filtering, completion short-circuit, dependencies + verifies blocking, dry-run continue behavior, QA invocation, startPacket, completePacket, and skipped/failed/completed semantics.
- run.ts still calls plan, develop, verify in the same order and preserves feature status/summary behavior.

### runVerifyPhase rename — FINE
No runtime caller still references qaPhase. rg only finds qaPhase in spec/docs/comments explaining the rename.

